You are analyzing HTTP traffic captured from a web application.
We are building MCP tools that let an AI agent call the app's APIs. A web app may use several independent APIs — its own backend, plus third-party services the frontend calls directly (e.g. Algolia for search, Mapbox for geocoding). We need all of them to get full coverage of the app's capabilities.

Identify all business API base URLs from the observed traffic.

A base URL can be:
- Just the origin: https://api.example.com
- Origin + path prefix: https://www.example.com/api

Rules:
- Include the app's own backend API AND third-party APIs called by the frontend for business features (search, maps, payments, etc.)
- Exclude infrastructure: CDN domains, analytics (google-analytics, hotjar, segment, etc.), ad trackers, font services, static asset hosts
- If the API endpoints share a common path prefix (e.g. /api/v1), include it
- A single URL called many times (e.g. POST /graphql) often indicates a GraphQL API — that's still a valid business API
- List the primary/most-important URL first
- Return each URL without trailing slash

